<p> the purpose </p>

<p> of </p>

<p> law laws and how </p>

<p> drug-related </p>

<p> behaviors can </p>

<p> affect the </p>

<p> balance </p>

<p> between the </p>

<p> need to </p>

<p> maintain </p>

<p> order and the </p>

<p> right of an </p>

<p> individual </p>

<p> 6 Day 5 follow-up Teacher </p>

<p> taught: </p>

<p> Focuses on </p>

<p> blood-alcohol </p>

<p> levels; uses </p>

<p> cooperative </p>

<p> learning </p>

<p> groups and </p>

<p> case studies </p>

<p> to </p>

<p> demonstrate </p>

<p> risks </p>

<p> involved in </p>

<p> drug abuse </p>

<p> 7 Drugs, media, and violence Officer </p>

<p> taught: </p>

<p> Focuses on </p>

<p> how drug </p>

<p> abuse and the </p>

<p> media can </p>

<p> increase </p>

<p> violent </p>

<p> behavior </p>

<p> 8,9 Managing anger and resolving Officer </p>

<p> taught: </p>

<p> Identifies </p>

<p> positive ways </p>

<p> conflict without drugs of expressing </p>

<p> and managing </p>

<p> anger without </p>

<p> the use of </p>

<p> drugs </p>

<p> 10 Day 8, 9 follow-up Teacher </p>

<p> taught: </p>

<p> Focuses on </p>

<p> the use of </p>

<p> &quot;I-message&quot; </p>

<p> statements </p>

<p> 11 Evaluation/Posttest Posttest of </p>

<p> students:=20 </p>

<p> Evaluation of </p>

<p> the program </p>

<p> by students </p>

<p> Exhibit 2.5 D.A.R.E.'s Parent Curriculum </p>

